10 An Act relating to public health; amending 63 O.S.
2021, Section 1-503, which relates to reports of
11 disease; updating statutory language and reference;
requiring addition of alpha-gal disease to list of
12 reportable conditions; making language gender
neutral; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-503, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 1-503. (A) A. The State Board Commissioner of Health
19 shall promulgate rules and regulations establishing a system of
20 reporting of cases of diseases diagnosed or detected by practicing
21 physicians and/or health care providers or clinical laboratories
22 which come within the purview of this article the Oklahoma Public
23 Health Code. A reporting system established by the Board
24 Commissioner shall be applicable to penal and eleemosynary
SB1644 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 inst itutions. Failure or refusal to report diseases as required by
2 the Board Commissioner shall constitute a misdemeanor.
3 (b) B. It shall be the duty of each local health officer to
4 report the existence of disease in his or her jurisdiction, as may
5 be required by rules and regulations of the State Board of Health.
6 C. The Commissioner shall add alpha-gal syndrome (AGS) to the
7 State Department of Health’s published list of reportable diseases
8 and conditions, the occurrence of which shall be reported to the
9 Department by a health care provider or clinical laboratory pursuant
10 to rules promulgated by the Commissioner.
11 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
12
13 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
OVERSIGHT, dated 04/16/2026 - DO PASS.
